Comment: This is an interesting move, it can lead to the Tarrasch Defence.
This is the von Hennig-Schara gambit
Queen goes back. White is a pawn up, but black as better development.
This is the most common move - stopping his knight from coming in on d4.
With nasty threats of N checking on c2 or maybe d3.

As is this move. I now had a long think. I considered Ba4, Kf1 and Ke2. What I played accidentally  gave back the pawn. After the game my opponent said that this is the best idea, but I am not convinced. Other moves seem OK looking at the opening databases. What I played leads to a pretty equal position, and maybe white should go after more.
